caption: Tried the new fried chicken sandwich. It was almost as good as the burger. Lovely people. Always busy. People gotta have their HB!
Simply one of the best burgers you'll ever eat!

Amazing burgers and the chicken sandwich is great too! Their unique fry sauce makes everything so much better and its not your standard ketchup/mayo mix. Always try their seasonal shake - they're delicious!
Big fat juicy burger, yes please!

My favorite place it town! Always grab extra fry sauce. I love sitting at the bar and watching the staff cook. Absolutely perfect burgers. The fries are always improving, they use to be only a means for eating fry sauce without people judging you, but they have come a long way and are really great in recent days. I also love their shakes—especially the seasonal ones. I could eat here every night.
Fantastic food, excellent customer service, no such thing as the perfect burger but pretty darn close.
Outstanding food and decent scarf selection

Really liked the concept of the place, it had a very urban feel...also the staff was super friendly. Went in in between 2-5pm so volume wasn't an issue, but we received simple looking but salty burger and overcooked fries. For $7 you could definitely score a better slab of grease from a local diner or even dare I say a fast food joint.  Oh and the Chocolate milkshake tasted more like a Chocolate flavored Icee 🤷🏽‍♂️  Not horrible, but definitely nothing to stay Humble about.
Fantastic burger and great atmosphere. Small menu is perfect.

One of our favorite places to eat BUT please enforce the mask mandate more. Your employees were great, but in the 15 minutes I was waiting for my amazing GF burger, I saw 4 individuals total not wearing masks at all and nothing was said to them. Its a small space, so I will probably not wait inside next time.  The GF buns are to die for!
Phenomenal burger shop. That's what they do. They make bomb burgers and a great selection of sides and they do it well. Great environment and friendly employees. P.S. their fry sauce is the best.
Hamburgers are amazing, fresh cut fries to die for!!! I tried the chai milkshake and loved it, going for the chocolate next time 💗
This restaurant is excellent!! Loved my burger and fries. Lots of tasty food. My son and I could have shared one order of fries. I highly recommend.

My son took us out to lunch at Humble Burger because he himself absolutely raves about how fresh, delicious and set apart theses burgers are;he was absolutely right! From the moment we walked into the shop we knew this place was different and in a good way. The customer service, wait time and food is absolutely stellar. Once our food arrived there was very little talking and a whole lot of enjoyment eating. The homemade ginger soda was delicious as was the double humble burger and fries. I loved the texture and crunchy edges of the burger along with the fresh hand crafted bun and all the incredibly flavorful ingredients..beautifully ✅ done. Next time we’re in town we will definitely come back. I would recommend Humble Burger to all my friends and family. You will not be disappointed. ❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️
The food was delicious, and the service was fast and friendly!  I will definitely be back!

Wow. I’ve never had a patty so crispy. A brioche bun toasted to perfection that doesn’t get soggy. The onion, sauce and pickles... I can’t even tell you what they’re doing in that kitchen. I bought a jar of their sauce just so I can experience the flavor whenever I want.  Let’s break it down: This is not everyone’s favorite burger. The patty is thin and crispy. Not very juicy. But it brings a nice contrast to the soft bun. The pickles are crisp and sweet. Again, they bring a contrast to the savory beef and sauce. The sauce itself is also a little sweet. It has some smokiness, some acidic notes and also the creaminess you expect from a burger sauce. Don’t forget to add cheese, because the original humble burger comes without.  I’m wishing Humble Burger long term success. 5/5 stars.
Favorite place to get a burger in town, or anywhere to be honest! High quality and friendly service!
Awesome Burger !!! Just wish they had more toppings :)

Best burgers in Idaho. Amazingly fresh ingredients, made fresh to order, perfectly seasoned, just the way you want it. The fries are amazingly crispy, beautifully seasoned. Their handmade sodas offer a refreshing alternative to your basic soda products and their chai milkshake is to die for! The ONLY thing I haven’t liked on their menu is their chicken nuggets- fumbly breading and not enough seasonings.
Very good burgers.  Fry sauce is also delicious.  Fries are amazing at times, but not consistent. Still 5 stars because the burgers.  Pricing is very reasonable.

Great burgers and fries. That’s all I eat when I go. I always ask for fresh, undercooked fries otherwise the fries are very hard and crunchy which is not my thing at all (Update - fries are cut thicker now making them perfect!).
Very delicious burgers, friendly staff and pay it forward, great place to eat or snack!

The only place I'm Moscow that does a dang smash burger right! Got the Lacey edges and everything! Also, Dem homemade pickles are really something special! 10/10 would recommend any day of the week! Maybe even more than once ;).
This place has the best burgers I've ever had. Nothing else to really say.
Always love humble burger! Best burger in town

Amazing burgers for a great price. There are a few burger places in town (that aren't fast food), and Humble stands out for a few reasons.  The cost is nice and low. The service is very fast. Their specific products are very good. And finally, the burgers are amazing, and a little unique. They have a nice crunch to them around the edges. I'm not sure how they cook them to be like that, but they're very good.
Love this place

Humble Burger is THE place to get THE best burger in Moscow. Hand made, fresh patties. Cooked to mouth watering perfection. Fantastic fresh cut fries. A variety of house sauces. And fresh gingerade. Seriously. Delish.

I’ve never had a bad experience at Humble Burger, their employee’s are always nice and the food is always good. Their chicken sandwich is my personal favorite and I think it’s comparable to Chick-Fil-A.
Best burger in Moscow, I get a double with extra sauce and pickles personally. Shakes are a bit over priced in my opinion. But everything you can get from here is good.
Super friendly staff. Insanely delicious burgers.  I think about humble burger far more than I am proud of.
Really good burgers and super nice staff!
Great quality meat and double patty for only $2 extra!!
So humble so burger.
Fantastic burgers! A must try if you’re ever in Moscow
I was not a huge fan of the extra crispiness of the burgers. Fries were average.
Outstanding burger with house special sauce. Shakes are great too.

Wonderful establishment. The burger that I received was well put together. Burger had a nice char to it, cooked well done, American cheese was used along with onions and 2 pickles(cucumbers) and all closed together with 2 toasted brioche buns. Burger was satisfying and tasted great but a little too pricey. I’d give it a 8/10. Cheers 🍻
Absolutely love this place. Excellent food at an excellent price. Always happy staff. Just awesome.
Very good burgers.
Great burger, awesome price

I desperately want to love Humble Burger. Moscow needs a truly great burger place and this just isn't it. I don't mind eating here but I just can't say that I love it. The rest of the evaluation is mostly a critique of the burger itself. The environment is very stylish and nice and the staff/ownership are very friendly and kind. Like I said, I want them to be great. Sadly, the food is just lacking.  1. The burgers are a decent portion and the meat is fresh but unfortunately the meat is also flavorless. They depend entirely on the toppings for flavoring the sandwich.  2. There's too much bread. The buns are too dense and it makes it all very dry. It's hard to enjoy the sandwich.  3. The prices are too high. To get fries, burger and drink you are looking at $10+. That's a bit steep for not getting a truly fantastic burger. Especially one that has lousy American cheese rather than a nice slice of medium cheddar.  4. The fries are fine but not spectacular. They are usually a bit overdone.  5. The frustrating thing is that the burgers were better when they started out at the farmer's market.  They have a nice little location but the food is just no longer worth the price.  Are you going to be mad if you eat here? Probably not. But will you feel like you could have spent that $10 on something better elsewhere? I would say so.
Best burgers in town. Fresh and quality.
Great service, great environment, & excellent burgers!
Best burger in town. Not the cheapest but super friendly service and great burgers and even better fry sauce
The burgers were really good, though I would not get a double again, it was way too much meat, especially since the bun was soooooo good.
Amazing burgers! You really can't beat them!
Small menu, super simple food, all done absolutely perfectly.  I couldn't be happier with the quality of the meat, how nice the staff is, or with the entire restaurant overall.
Really great burgers. One of the best lunch places in Moscow.

I have enjoyed Humble Burger since the day it opened, in fact I ate there for 3 days straight the day it did.   I absolutely LOVED these style burgers and was very grateful to have something like this in Moscow.  However, I just ordered delivery through door dash today, and let me say it was one of the worst meals I have TRIED to eat.  The fries were burned (also not the same fries as the previous few times I ordered)  There was a MASSIVE amount of onions, and only 2 pickles.  The flattened burger was burned on the outer brim (WAY more than usual, and you could just smell the burning smell before I even opened the bag.  The bun they use now seems like it came from WINCO.  EVERYTHING is different, everything is wrong.  Please be weary that nothing about this restaurant is the same since opening, and the change is horrible.  I will not eat here again.

Really really excellent burgers, pretty good fries. Nice, small dinner style sit down area. Our favorite burger place for whole family, everyone gets a cheese burger and we share a couple orders of fries. Well worth it.
Such amazing food! Come here all the time and whenever I have friends in from out of town this is my number one place to take them. Simple and awesome. Definitely recommend!!!
Not gonna lie, humble burger is the best burger in the world! The burger, ginger-lemon soda, nuggets, slaw, everything is really good!
It's nice that the menu is small enough that I don't have to stand there and say "can I get uhhhhhhhh" for ten minutes.
Always excellent. Recommended.

Love this burger joint. Simple menu, courteous service, and flavorful burgers and fries. The burgers are hand made, as are the fries and both taste delicious. Craft cider and beer from local artisans are also served, and the dining room is clean and comfy. If you are addicted to burgers, as am I, this is a must stop in Moscow.  My fave is the double humble burger with fries.
Great burger's, great team, great shakes, worth stopping by.
Excellent burgers made with fresh regional and local ingredients! They have yummy milkshakes too....
Loved the cheeseburger! Fantastic hand made patty was fantastic! The coleslaw was just so so. The lemonade was good but small.

This is where my boyfriend and I had our first date on January 2nd 2018. We've been together for two years now, but I can still remember how magical that night was, and how it wouldn't have been the same, if he hadn't taken me to a restaurant that's close to his heart, and a characteristic fixture in his childhood town.

Clean building with an open layout. The grill is prominently on display in the center of the restaurant. Burgers where delicious and service was very friendly and fast. This is now my go-to burger joint.
Best burger place in Moscow! Simple menu and you can't go wrong!
Great burgers!!! The chicken nuggets are honestly pretty gross. Milkshake was a bit watery, not very milk-shake like. But burgers and fries and the humble burger sauce is fabulous.

They were nice and fast. For a cooked to order burger it was faster than expected. They girl working the register was nice and helpful. The location was clean and inviting.  However the food did not live up to the service or speed. The fry sauce they put on the burgers and offer with fries is horrible. The burger was ok. The hero was the pre packaged bun.
Delicious burger and fries!
Great burgers and fries. Their fry sauce is amazing.
Really nice reasonably priced burgers.

We found this restaurant online and decided to try it. We had a little trouble finding it using Google maps. The outside is very appealing. The inside was okay. We ordered a #1 Humble burger with fries and lemonade. It comes with special sauce. We tried the fry sauce and the ranch dressing with the fries. The ranch dressing was really good as was the fry sauce. The burger was good too. The lemonade was strong but good. The only problem was that the drink was to small.
Delicious food that is clearly made with a lot of heart, good drink choices, yummy ranch, good atmosphere and friendly staff.  Edited to say: the crispiness on the edges of the burger are delightful
If you like your hamburger buns hard and burnt (all 3 burgers that I ordered were like this.) and you don't mind spending 2.25 on a tiny cup of tasteless slaw then this is your place.
Easily the best burger place in the Palouse. The burgers and milkshakes are spectacular.
Great burger!!!  Small place...HUGE Flavor!
My son and I had been eating humble burgers at the farmers market. We finally visited the restaurant. It is a cute little spot with great burgers!
Undrwealming. Chicken nuggets odd texture and taste. Shakes not great.
The best veggie burger I've ever had.

It's a burger place, but it's worth noting that the people were great and there is a good selection of beer. Aside from that, burger was filling and good. I'm not normally a fan of sweet pickles, but theirs pairs very well. I am a fan of onions, but I recommend asking for light or be prepared to take some off. They really overload it and they aren't grilled or anything. DON'T GET THE SLAW. It's such a small serving it is a joke and not worth giving up the fries. Seriously, get nothing rather than the slaw. I'd come here again, no doubt. It's a little pricey, but it's a good local spot
If you go at lunch time the line is shorter, and the dinner line is very long all the time. Besides that the food is amazing.
Humble would be great, but this is just very greasy and overpriced.
Really great simple burgers
Fast service and always amazing food!!
Awesome burgers and awesome place to hang out!
Small, local eatery with the best fries around.
Really friendly staff.  Easy going atmosphere. But... just too much salt on our burgers !  We heard another table commenting about the over salting, also.   But will definitely go back !
Really good burgers and awsome milkshake too plus the fries are delicious as well
This is a favorite stop for us after walking the Farmers' Market in downtown Moscow.  Tasty burgers and fries.  Family operated business.
Difficult to find on the first visit but low key top notch burger joint. Go for the meat!
One of the best burgers on the Palouse.
Burgers were not bad but buns were quite dry.  Good lemonade and pretty good fries.  Wait times were quite long and seating is limited.
Great burgers
Awesome burger!
Good food.  Similar to Smashburger.
The lettuce wraps are excellent.  Worth the wait for fresh food.
Fantastic food w/fantastic service
Wonderful homemade burgers, super fries and sauce and homemade lemonade drinks!
Great atmosphere and friendly staff. Burger was excellent! Only negative was to much salt on the fries, which is a bummer because the fries themselves are excellent the way they are prepared.
Awesome hamburger and fries.
Too much bun.
Food: 90/100 Service: 90/100 Venue: 90/100  Very good burger, well seasoned, and juicy. Fries under cooked for my taste.
Great little lunch spot. The burgers were amazing.
Liked it a lot...good grub...must try if you are in the area!
Amazing smash burger cooked perfectly, tasty mustard-y fry sauce, relaxed atmosphere... the best burger place in the area!

The hommade burger part is nice, but its an expensive burger with none of the toppings, which is good for those that like meat and bread. I am not like that. A pretentious and yuppie atmosphere, but staff seemed nice.
Great burger! Can't Wait for a return trip to Moscow.
They have good burgers 👍
Loved it, great place to eat with friends
Delicious summer meal! and this all for $12. Simple menu, quality ingredients, friendly service. Slaw has been fermented, healthy and more filling than the lil cup looks.

Cozy straight forward hamburger joint. The process are great the food is very fresh very homemade and extremely good. Clean friendly. Definitely going to become a regular customer and highly recommend to others

I am a chef, and everything about this restaurant is fantastic! I make almost an hour trip just to treat myself, friends, and family to a humble burger. The customer service is always on point, they handle unexpected rushes with grace, and always have a very clean and unique atmosphere. I just can't get enough. This restaurant, by far, is an absolute must try if you are passing through or are a local that has never been.

My son from Calif was visiting my daughter and they went to eat burgers. My son got his lettuce wrap and found a little slug crawling. My daughter went up to the counter and the young man says oh sorry, I can give you another piece of lettuce! Who does that, maybe offer a refund, a free burger next time? We wont be going back

Humble burger was so good with simple ingredients! I highly recommend the fry sauce as well, it was unexpectedly flavorful and a little spicy maybe as well. I added on a milkshake, and I totally did not regret it. I will definitely be back for more and hoping for another seasonal flavor of milkshake next time.

So a bunch of buzz about how good Humble Burgers was, I decided to give them a try. I could not have been more disappointed. The big secret to their success seems to be... Salt, on everything. I couldn't eat more than two of the fries. And the burgers were so salty, my stomach was upset for rest of the night. I recommend avoiding Humble Burgers unless you want to eat salt with a side of food.
The food is terrible, the service is slow and rude, and they can't manage their time or resources correctly.

Some of the best burgers in town while still being reasonably priced. I love how the patties are just the right thickness: thick enough to be juicy in the middle but still thin enough so that the edges start to get a little crispy. Not to mention that the housemade fry sauce is the bomb diggity. All round great spot for a lunch or dinner out. Keep up the quality work, Humble Burger.
The burgers were excellent but fries were really salty and they have off brand soda and no soda fountain...pretty expensive as well
Food was SO GOOD. So simple but delicious!!
One of the best burgers I've ever had. There is something about the Humble Burger sauce that makes you want to come back for more
Delicious burgers and fries. Great fry sauce.
Great burgers at a decent price.
Great burgers and fries. Not a fan of anything else on the menu and pretty spendy.

The Burgers are Great! Everything else? Not so good. My kid got chicken nuggets and ate one and had enough. They tasted like a Italian chicken meat ball breaded, bad chinese sweet and sour pork. The fries were rubbery and burnt. The burgers, that is what saved this from a 1 star for sure.
Best burger I've ever, and I've probably eaten thousands of burgers in various parts of the word. Glad to be a regular. The fries are a tad thin but overall I like them.
Simple and delicious!
We had a double each and it was A-1.

I've been to Humble Burger a few times now, and have yet to be disappointed. They have amazing, flavorful burgers and friendly staff members. The only downsides is that it is a pretty small dining area, and in my opinion there milkshakes aren't the best. Bottom line: I would definitely recommend.
Cheap good burger. Spend the extra 3 bucks and get the burger here instead of McDonalds.

It's clear they have a definite "thing" they want to pull off.  It's "slow food" in a way, since they don't take call in orders.  That is, they're still pretty fast but it is fun to watch them craft a burger and the environment is great to just hang out at.  They also contribute a music venue to Moscow, expanding on what is a surprisingly vibrant scene for this small town.
Best in town. Period
Great burgers/fries and milkshakes. The ginger lemonade is delicious and I love the choices of ciders and beers.
The burgers are incredible, fries are okay and the chai shake had great flavor (but was more the consistency of a frappuccino).
Burger hits the spot!
Awesome, fun little place. Great burger and nice pay it forward idea!

Such a cozy little diner! Simple and DELICIOUS.  We sat at the high top counter and watched them make the burgers from scratch. I am a vegetarian and ordered the veggie burger (falafel based) with humble sauce....so. freaking. good. My husband ordered the humble cheeseburger and said it was fantastic.  Try the coleslaw, it's made with fresh red peppers and the dressing is tangy and sweet. Drink options include local beers and ciders and soft drinks. Fun place for a date night or to watch the locals. Will be going back.
Amazing hamburgers, everything is fresh.
Nice, old school burgers
Good Food, small building, kinda expensive
I want another one. It's... It's just so beautiful 😭
This restaurant sells the best I burgers in the region. Great prices and low wait time.

HB is the best burger in town for the price! Amazing atmosphere, fast and friendly service. My only regret is the amount of times I've walked over on a Monday only to remember they're closed. Don't forget to try their house lemonade and rotating shake flavors!
Good food, good service, good time. Worth trying :)
Not Humble by any means, but amazing nonetheless.
Decent burgers, fries were so overcooked I couldn't eat them. My hunger was satisfied!
Great food made by great people
Really good burgers
Best burger in Moscow!
Sooooo goooood. Try all the milkshakes too!
This place has really, really good burger and their sauce is amazing!
The burgers here were amazing. Some of the best burgers I have had in my life. The meat quality is phenomenal. The only downside is there is not a lot of space, and it can fill up quickly.
Best burgers on the Palouse. Frys and fry sauce are out of this world.
Delicious burgers here and good fries.
Phenomenal Experience!  The food/atmosphere/staff are all amazing. This is hands down the home to the best burgers in town. 17.5 out of 10 recommend this spot fosho.

Good burgers and food, pretty small building that fills up pretty quick. A regular vs a large fry doesn't look like much but their fries are pretty small so it's actually a lot more fries in a regular than it looks like. Overall, great burgers made with great ingredients
Great burgers. I just wished they had more traditional drinks. Fry sauce and the HB sauce is awesome.

Such a unique burger place. The fries and burgers have a flavor that you will not find in any other crevice of the world. There is a lot of seating and the prices are fair. George works here, which makes my four star review into a five star review. Not biased, just happy with the service.
Great staff! Place has an awesome vibe and the food is really good.
Best burger and fries I've ever had
Awesome food

I love this place! The burgers are reasonably priced and they source their ingredients from the local co-op. I've ran into the guys at the co-op, so I know it's true. I try to eat beef only once a week and this is what I end up choosing for that weekly beef meal 9 times out of 10. They make the burgers in front of you right after you order them (smash patty style) and their sauce is something I've literally had dreams about. They know it's good and have recently started selling their sauce by the jar. I can always count on friendly conversation with the employees anytime I go in there and good music. Also, if you frequent the establishment they make an effort to remember you although that doesn't change the service because it can't get any better than it is. For the people my age who will understand this, it's the closet you will ever come in life to eating a Krabby Patty. If you've never eaten here before you need to change that!
Burger's are good, fries are garbage.
It's an average burger at an above average price! (Almost as good as McDonalds not even close to Carl's Jr.)

We have known Humble Burgers since years ago when they have (and still do) a stand at the Moscow's Farmers Market. Their burgers were awesome, especially the meat and pickles. Don't forget the fry sauce!! Recent additions to the menu was unbelievably great as well, with lemonade, fries, and milkshakes top others in my opinion. We are regulars and definitely recommend this place!!
Super good burgers and fries!
The burger is amazing and the veggie burger is also great. The fries are thin and crispy, and the fry sauce is worth getting. Plus, the bathrooms are nice and clean.
Nice burgers, fries are very meh.

The burgers are good. Fries are good. Good selection of beer. The chicken nuggets are a little strange, but I was raised to avoid chicken nuggets, so maybe mom was on to something. Your mom could have raised you differently, no judgments here. Try the nuggets for yourself, I guess. Overall, I could probably be talked into going again some time, which is saying something.
True to their name, Humble Burger doesn't have a lot of options on their menu, but what they do, they do well.
Delicious burgers! A little pricey for just a burger and fries, but it was definitely a good experience.
Theres no thrills to this burger, it's simply made and delicious. The ingredients taste fresh. I love their pickles. Their fry sauce is really good. Haven't had their shakes, but hoping to try soon
Great burgers and fries, slightly expensive but worth it.

Obviously they have the best burgers in the PNW. That’s indisputable. I’d like to point out how good their janitor work is. For such a greasy place everything is consitently shinier than the top of the Chrysler building.
Amazing burgers!
Best burger in the area!! Simple and delicious burger, great shakes and fries. Me and my buddy came there on a whim and have been frequenting the place ever since.

I absolutely love their burgers and fries! Their pickles are delicious I always ask for extra. Their sauce is addicting. And the buns are so good. I have nothing negative about the quality and taste of the food! I wish it didn't take as long and that they were able to have more grill space and employees in order to speed up the process. Also it would be nice if there was more seating. I've gone in at a busy time and waited over 20 min for 2 burgers and fries and then there was nowhere to sit. Hopefully they expand and hire more employees

Amazing burgers, fun atmosphere, awesome staff. Humber Burker is one of those places you always have an amazing burger and experience!  Photo: from their Farmers Market stand. I'll post a photo of their permanent location later.
Great special sauce on burgers!
Love the atmosphere and the delicious made from scratch and locally sourced foods and drinks.
Delicious.
Clean cost atmosphere.  Friendly courteous staff.
Great burgers and fries! Highly recommend!!
I have never wanted to thank America so much until I had a humble burger. I truly understand how humble this burger is. Because everyone should know about the best burger ever made.
Always amazing never had a bad burger from here always fresh off the grill.
Great burgers but fries and drink selection were not good at all.  Fix that and I'd give it a 5.
Busy place, usually indicates good food. Handmade burgers, fries and sodas. Sort of a hipster vibe. Small dining room.
Very good food. Supports local resources..

The burger was straight up delicious. I recommend it. They cook the fries longer than most other restaurants; my wife liked the fries, but I thought they were overcooked. I also got a chocolate shake, which was not what I was expecting. The shake was heavy on the coco, and not so heavy on the sugar so it was almost a savory shake. I could see how some fancy people would enjoy it, but I didn't as much. Next time I will get their house made soda instead. The place is on the expensive side with two combo meals, one with a shake, totaling $27.43. The environment is busy, and the place is small, add to the hustle and bustle. It's a nice place to go, but you may not be able to get a table to sit at.
Ok

Fun neighborhood place! But, the price seems high for what it is. Asking premium burger prices for barely above fast food. 5 guys, and in and out both have significantly better burgers for equal or lesser $$ 😢
Easily one of the best burgers I’ve had. Friendly service too.
Amazing homemade burgers flipped by some amazing folks. They have their own take on sauce that is addictive.  Worth the stop.

I consider myself a burger connoisseur, and have had the very best in different states across the country and also like to grill my own gourmet creations very frequently. I was skeptical about their burger topping philosophy, i.e. "Our menu isn't this way because we think we have the best burger around and no other toppings need apply"; however, i was quite impressed with the texture and taste and it wasn't a sloppy soggy mess. The beef was quite delicious. Very good job! That being said, It would be awesome to see other topping choices like bacon, jalapenos other kinds of cheese, etc. Why limit yourself?

If you ever find yourself in Idaho this is THEE burger place to go. It has a menu as small as In & Out but the food is far more delicious! The fries seem to be cut by staff and the fry sauce also seems to be made from scratch, I. Love. It! I am a burger fanatic & this is way better than any over rated burger joint I’ve ever been to.
This place is great. Burgers are deceptively large.
Simple, cooked to perfection, and a perfectly cooked bun. No BS, just a good burger.

This is a beautifully simple place with a beautifully simple menu and one of the best tasting, most worthy burgers you are likely to find anytime soon. It's amazing what you can achieve by using superior quality ingredients. The flavor of these burgers is extraordinary and the prices are really fair for what you get.
Their fry sauce is so tasty that we carry it around in our car! Thank you humble burger for always covering our fry sauce needs we appreciate you.
Excellent burger with perfect bun!
Excellent food at an affordable price for occasional outings. I love coming here for a date with my wife while visiting family in Moscow.
Absolutely wonderful!
Excellent burger
This place is awesome. No fuss, just a great burger and fries plus homemade fry sauce that's so much better than the nasty ketchup and mayo.
Good alternative to fast food. Homemade sodas are excellent. Service is fast and friendly.
A wholesome burger place with unique taste! I just wish there was more on their menu!
I love the humble burger.... I love the homemade pickles. Nom nom nom nom nom. Great place to eat.
Best place in Moscow to get a hamburger.
Great tasting burger and fries. Will be a regular stop when we visit Moscow.
very nice, cost effective burger
Best burger on the Palouse!
Favorite burgers in town
Love it! However, the fries weren't my favorite.
Awesome
This place is great.  If you want an outstanding no-frills hamburger and fries you owe it to yourself to check out Humble Burger.  Best I've had!
Great burger and great sauce! They also do lettuce wraps which is rare in Moscow or Pullman!
It's a very good burger. The taste combination is just perfect and i wish you had a pdx location!

Saw their kiosk while visiting the street fair. Later, after perusing the whole fair, we decided we would hit a couple of antique stores.  After shopping decided that a lettuce wrap burger would be fine for lunch and started looking for a parking spot to walk to the kiosk. Upon parking, discovered we were right in front of the actual restaurant! Went in, placed our order and retreated to the outside tables. We were second in a line of two....but within a few minutes, the place was jammed out the far door. It was one of the best burgers we have enjoyed in quite awhile, big...juicy...caramelized on both sides but still moist in the middle.  Just like you would fix one at home in the cast iron skillet.  We will definitely will be back when we're in the area, we visit Lewiston yearly.
Simple and delicious!!! I go to Humble on rough days at work as a pick me up. I wouldn’t go around noon because the line will be long.
Best burger in Moscow by far. Hours are a lil whack, but it's trendy so it kind of makes sense
These are great burgers, nothing fancy or anything specialty added.  Just meat cheese and homemade pickles. I do wish they had lettuce and tomato and more pickles
Quality ingredients. Great folks!

The burgers are great! It was one of the best burgers I've had. There isn't anything different added, it is just a great burger. The fries are nice and thin which makes them crunchy. You can get any burger without the bun if you don't want the carbs or gluten.  The people are very nice and helpful. They were very accommodating for some of our special requests, and were about to help with some of the special requests.  The place is not large, but the place is nice for a burger.
Yummy burgersfor sure only thing was all they offered American cheese. Also the fries are thin and dry
This was the best burger ever! Love this place.
Fantastic! Wonderfully simple and perfectly delicious.
Very good.
Well worth the cost!
Perfect burgers
Great little place! Awesome food!
To be fair, my son over sold me on the burgers. They are certainly good, but they need a little help on creating a lettuce wrap. Very tasty though.
Always friendly staff, great product.
Not the easiest place to find but great burgers.

Burger is delicious, but pretty pricey. The milkshakes are like chocolate smoothies... Gross!!  It doesn’t taste like there is any milk, it’s like ice and chocolate syrup. The milkshakes are super gross. Other than that, tasty burgers!
The Best!
WOW!!! What great burgers!!
Very good, homemade hamburgers, will definitely go back
Best burger I've found in Moscow in the 13 years I've lived here.

This burger joint is AMAZING. It has a pleasant interior, where the cooks fire up patties on a grill that is in view. Burgers. . . the burgers are wonderful. Their fries are a bit strange; they are cooked to a crisp and do not have much "meat," but they oddly seem to work with these burgers. I highly recommend this place.

We came in right before closing and the service was excellent! The food was amazing - probably the best in Moscow. They make it fresh right in front of you! My only regret is only getting one burger!  Edit: I no longer go to this establishment, as I heard it was affiliated with the notorious Christchurch. I am sure the food is still delicious and the customer service was always great, but I can't support such hateful ideology. Christchurch already owns so much of this town, and I don't like contributing to them if I can help it.
Great burger buns and fresh tasting burger
Best burger ever
Best burger and fries in the whole world, you will absolutely not be disappointed.
Baller place. Awesome food. Dope people. Keep it up.
Super salty, overcooked frite style frys.  The burger was decent for rapid food
My favorite burger place in town. Burgers are great, fries have lots of salt, and the fry sauce is is amazing.
Had a double burger. It was outstanding. They cook with fresh ground beef and not frozen patties.
Really good! Local meat, all grass fed and delicious. My favortite burger place ever!
Yummy burgers!!

Surprisingly pricy. BUT the burgers are great. Coleslaw is not what you normally think of as coleslaw, and my wife, who loves coleslaw, too one bite and there the rest in the trash. So that is not for everybody. Fries were great. Fry sauce was great. Excellent service as well.
The veggie burger was pretty good! Not too often can you say that about a veggie burger.
Great burgers

The burgers were good! There are only canned drinks or lemonade. We looked up the restaurant based on $ suggestion and this restaurant was rated "reasonably priced". For our family of four (one of which is 1yr old) it was nearly $40. They offer local meat from the co-op so Im sure their cost for product is higher and is of quality (we just did not know that based off of previous reviews). This is not your average burger joint, if youre looking for milkshakes this is not the place. They have a specific mission in their quality of product unlike other restaurants, give them a try!
Best burger in town! They have a delicious house made habanero fry sauce!

The burgers were well seasoned and quite good. You can see Tam take the beef and cook and season it in front of you. They seem to make a lot of their menu in house, so that's also a plus. Overall, a good, inexpensive burger joint.
A new must have in Moscow, great burgers and excellent service.

Burgers done right. A little on the spendy side for a burger, but totally worth it and understandable when you take the first bite. Locally owned. Almost everything is homemade and delicious! My kids were blown away by the homemade applesauce and pickles.
First time and it was great

The burger was good. Great flavor, but the bun was extremely dry. The fries were really over cooked. Super crispy that kind of hurts your mouth after eating a couple of them. :/ Fry sauce was good and I could actually use my over cooked 'knife fry' to spread the sauce on my bun which helped. A little over priced for what was served. The staff was friendly and service was fantastic.
Very limited menu, but what's offered is pretty good. Closes too early in the evenings.
The food was amazing and the establishment was clean and very modern looking
Local ingredients, fast friendly service.
So good, so cool, and so many stocking caps...
Excellent veggie burger
Everything is delicious!! My favorite is a cheeseburger with fries and a chai milkshake
Yummy burger with a delicious and well seasoned patty. Simple, delicious, filling meal. I added on fry sauce and slaw.
Best burger in town. And the fry sauce is to die for
Just one great burger! Simple, yummy.

This is a great local place with awesome well priced burgers and cheap local shows. Not a big fan of the fries, but you can buy everything individually. They're also adding to their menu as well. They also hosted and organized the modest musicfest and which was really sweet.

They close at 8:00. I was there 7:45. They told me they only can do take away! I think the normal way is not letting customers in at 8:00 and serve those who are there before 8:00. [after we had our dinner elsewhere, we saw lots of people were in the restaurant at 9:00]  So, I think I will not be supporting them anymore.

Good food. Always opt for the double Patty. Good service. Good fry sauce. The one gripe is very occasionally the point of sale system they have lags and slows down the process.
Great burgers and fries. It is one of my favorites in the region.
Delicious burger and fries (the fry sauce is to die for). Super friendly staff. Will definitely be back!
OMG, has to he my favorite place to eat in Moscow.
Had a great burger. The slaw was unique and good.
Fantastic Burgers and fries. Not fast food.
Went here almost every Friday, and despite the limited menu I never got bored of their burgers. Very good prices for the juiciest burgers in town.
Tasty fresh burger (really good pickles!). Good fries. The sparkling ginger lemonade was zippy and refreshing. Awesome service!
There is only one kind of burger but it's great

I didn't think I would like the pickles on the burger,  but the sauce, pickles and fresh hamburger meat are a winning combination. Have been here several times and have enjoyed it every time. Try the homemade lemonade, it's awesome.
Not bad. Limited selection, but what they have is good. Slightly pricey for what you get.

Humble is the best way to describe it. The staff (family and family friend owned) was the two brothers, fun, social and happy to answer my many questions! Menu is super simple and easy to read and prices are very reasonable. All local ingredients even the buns are dropped off in the morning from a local baker just down the street and pickles and 'special sauce' are made in house! If you get the opportunity to eat here take it and talk to the friendly staff while they cook right in front of you!
Ok burger place
Delicious!

This is my favorite burger place of all time! I love this place so much... Mmmmmmm
Simple menu and hospitable staff! Traditional burger and fries establishment with free seating and  live music.

Absolutely freaking if I ever come back to Moscow I will definitely be eating here! I am SO full and haven't even had my fries! Family owned and run, this is a place to go! Including a pay it forward  post(with help from the local food bank)! Don't be greedy feed the needy!
